description: Get information about an Amazon Q Business data source connector synchronization.

parameters.name: dataSourceId
parameters.description: The identifier of the data source connector.

parameters.name: applicationId
parameters.description: The identifier of the Amazon Q Business application connected to the data source.

parameters.name: indexId
parameters.description: The identifier of the index used with the Amazon Q Business data source connector.

nested_items.name: history
nested_items.description: A history of synchronization jobs for the data source connector.

nested_items.name: executionId
nested_items.description: The identifier of a data source synchronization job.

nested_items.name: startTime
nested_items.description: The Unix time stamp when the data source synchronization job started.

nested_items.name: endTime
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the synchronization job completed.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the synchronization job. When the Status field is set to SUCCEEDED, the synchronization job is done. If the status code is FAILED, the ErrorCode and ErrorMessage fields give you the reason for the failure.

nested_items.name: errorMessage
nested_items.description: The message explaining the Amazon Q Business request error.

nested_items.name: errorCode
nested_items.description: The code associated with the Amazon Q Business request error.

nested_items.name: dataSourceErrorCode
nested_items.description: If the reason that the synchronization failed is due to an error with the underlying data source, this field contains a code that identifies the error.

nested_items.name: documentsAdded
nested_items.description: The current count of documents added from the data source during the data source sync.

nested_items.name: documentsModified
nested_items.description: The current count of documents modified in the data source during the data source sync.

nested_items.name: documentsDeleted
nested_items.description: The current count of documents deleted from the data source during the data source sync.

nested_items.name: documentsFailed
nested_items.description: The current count of documents that failed to sync from the data source during the data source sync.

nested_items.name: documentsScanned
nested_items.description: The current count of documents crawled by the ongoing sync job in the data source.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, Amazon Q Business returns this token. You can use this token in any subsequent request to retrieve the next set of jobs.
